    <h1>Are Good & Gather Chocolate Chips Gluten-Free? A Comprehensive Guide</h1>

    <p>When it comes to baking, chocolate chips are a staple ingredient in many households. Whether you're making cookies, brownies, or muffins, the quality and ingredients of your chocolate chips matter. For those with gluten sensitivities or celiac disease, ensuring that your chocolate chips are gluten-free is crucial. In this article, we’ll dive deep into whether Good & Gather chocolate chips are gluten-free, what to look for on the label, and how to safely incorporate them into your gluten-free baking.</p>

    <h2>Understanding Gluten and Its Impact</h2>

    <p>Gluten is a protein found in wheat, barley, rye, and triticale. For individuals with celiac disease or gluten sensitivity, consuming gluten can lead to a range of symptoms, from digestive issues to long-term health complications. Therefore, it’s essential to carefully scrutinize food labels to ensure that products are free from gluten-containing ingredients.</p>

    <p>Chocolate chips, in their purest form, are typically made from cocoa solids, sugar, and sometimes added fats like cocoa butter. However, cross-contamination during manufacturing or the addition of flavorings and stabilizers can introduce gluten into the product. This is why it’s important to verify the gluten-free status of any chocolate chips you plan to use in your baking.</p>

